      "id": "full-picture",
      "title": "The Full Picture",
      "description": "You've now seen how secure-exec is built: a core package defining types and the bridge layer, platform-specific execution drivers (Node, Browser, Python, WASM), a deny-by-default permission model governed by behavioral contracts, a three-tier testing strategy ensuring parity with host Node.js, and comprehensive documentation. The architecture is designed for modularity — new runtimes slot in behind the same RuntimeDriver interface. Explore the codebase and check the contracts in .agent/contracts/ for the authoritative specification.",
